gues. By the time of Etkind’s death, he did not rework these essays into a continuous narrative. Originally published in Russian, this first-ever English translation prepared by Etkind’s daughter presents his memoirs as a document of his time, without any changes or abridgements. The editors’ additions are limited to several notes, proofreading of "es, and checking or inserting the full forms of the characters’ names.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh  aIntellectual life.  aLeningrad school of literature theory.  aRussian Literature.  aRussian Poetry and Translation.  aintelligentsia in Soviet Union.1 aBethea, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBethea, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMan, Joyse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReeve, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrubikhina, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076741408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644697924?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/